\title{Perplexity Search}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Perform AI-powered web searches with real-time information using Perplexity models via LiteLLM and OpenRouter. This skill should be used when conducting web searches for current information, finding recent scientific literature, getting grounded answers with source citations, or accessing information beyond the model's knowledge cutoff. Provides access to multiple Perplexity models including Sonar Pro, Sonar Pro Search (advanced agentic search), and Sonar Reasoning Pro through a single OpenRouter API key.}

\subtree{
\title{Perplexity Search}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Perform AI-powered web searches using Perplexity models through LiteLLM and OpenRouter. Perplexity provides real-time, web-grounded answers with source citations, making it ideal for finding current information, recent scientific literature, and facts beyond the model's training data cutoff.}

\p{This skill provides access to all Perplexity models through OpenRouter, requiring only a single API key (no separate Perplexity account needed).}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{Use this skill when:}

\ul{
\li{Searching for current information or recent developments (2024 and beyond)}
\li{Finding latest scientific publications and research}
\li{Getting real-time answers grounded in web sources}
\li{Verifying facts with source citations}
\li{Conducting literature searches across multiple domains}
\li{Accessing information beyond the model's knowledge cutoff}
\li{Performing domain-specific research (biomedical, technical, clinical)}
\li{Comparing current approaches or technologies}
}

\p{\strong{Do not use} for:}

\ul{
\li{Simple calculations or logic problems (use directly)}
\li{Tasks requiring code execution (use standard tools)}
\li{Questions well within the model's training data (unless verification needed)}
}
}

