\li{Create account and generate API key}
\li{\startverb Add credits to account (minimum $5 recommended)\stopverb}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Configure environment}:}
}

\subtree{
\title{Or use setup script}
\p{python scripts/setup_env.py --api-key sk-or-v1-your-key-here}

\pre{\startverb

3. **Install dependencies**:
\stopverb}

\p{uv pip install litellm}

\pre{\startverb

4. **Verify setup**:
\stopverb}

\p{python scripts/perplexity_search.py --check-setup}

\pre{\startverb

See `references/openrouter_setup.md` for detailed setup instructions, troubleshooting, and security best practices.

\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Basic Usage}
\p{\strong{Simple search:}}

\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py "What are the latest developments in CRISPR gene editing?"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Save results:}}

\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py "Recent CAR-T therapy clinical trials" --output results.json
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Use specific model:}}

\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py "Compare mRNA and viral vector vaccines" --model sonar-pro-search
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Verbose output:}}

\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py "Quantum computing for drug discovery" --verbose
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Available Models}
\p{Access models via \code{\startverb --model\stopverb} parameter:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{sonar-pro} (default): General-purpose search, best balance of cost and quality}
\li{\strong{sonar-pro-search}: Most advanced agentic search with multi-step reasoning}
\li{\strong{sonar}: Basic model, most cost-effective for simple queries}
\li{\strong{sonar-reasoning-pro}: Advanced reasoning with step-by-step analysis}
\li{\strong{sonar-reasoning}: Basic reasoning capabilities}
}

\p{\strong{Model selection guide:}}

\ul{
\li{Default queries → \code{\startverb sonar-pro\stopverb}}
\li{Complex multi-step analysis → \code{\startverb sonar-pro-search\stopverb}}
\li{Explicit reasoning needed → \code{\startverb sonar-reasoning-pro\stopverb}}
\li{Simple fact lookups → \code{\startverb sonar\stopverb}}
\li{Cost-sensitive bulk queries → \code{\startverb sonar\stopverb}}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/model_comparison.md\stopverb} for detailed comparison, use cases, pricing, and performance characteristics.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Crafting Effective Queries}
\subtree{
\title{Be Specific and Detailed}
\p{\strong{Good examples:}}

\ul{
\li{"What are the latest clinical trial results for CAR-T cell therapy in treating B-cell lymphoma published in 2024?"}
\li{"Compare the efficacy and safety profiles of mRNA vaccines versus viral vector vaccines for COVID-19"}
\li{"Explain AlphaFold3 improvements over AlphaFold2 with specific accuracy metrics from 2023-2024 research"}
}

\p{\strong{Bad examples:}}

\ul{
\li{"Tell me about cancer treatment" (too broad)}
\li{"CRISPR" (too vague)}
\li{"vaccines" (lacks specificity)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Include Time Constraints}
\p{Perplexity searches real-time web data:}

\ul{
\li{"What papers were published in Nature Medicine in 2024 about long COVID?"}
\li{"What are the latest developments (past 6 months) in large language model efficiency?"}
\li{"What was announced at NeurIPS 2023 regarding AI safety?"}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Specify Domain and Sources}
\p{For high-quality results, mention source preferences:}

\ul{
\li{"According to peer-reviewed publications in high-impact journals..."}
\li{"Based on FDA-approved treatments..."}
\li{"From clinical trial registries like clinicaltrials.gov..."}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Structure Complex Queries}
\p{Break complex questions into clear components:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Topic}: Main subject}
\li{\strong{Scope}: Specific aspect of interest}
\li{\strong{Context}: Time frame, domain, constraints}
\li{\strong{Output}: Desired format or type of answer}
}

\p{\strong{Example:} "What improvements does AlphaFold3 offer over AlphaFold2 for protein structure prediction, according to research published between 2023 and 2024? Include specific accuracy metrics and benchmarks."}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/search_strategies.md\stopverb} for comprehensive guidance on query design, domain-specific patterns, and advanced techniques.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Use Cases}
\subtree{
\title{Scientific Literature Search}
\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py \
  "What does recent research (2023-2024) say about the role of gut microbiome in Parkinson's disease? Focus on peer-reviewed studies and include specific bacterial species identified." \
  --model sonar-pro
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Technical Documentation}
\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py \
  "How to implement real-time data streaming from Kafka to PostgreSQL using Python? Include considerations for handling backpressure and ensuring exactly-once semantics." \
  --model sonar-reasoning-pro
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Comparative Analysis}
\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py \
  "Compare PyTorch versus TensorFlow for implementing transformer models in terms of ease of use, performance, and ecosystem support. Include benchmarks from recent studies." \
  --model sonar-pro-search
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Clinical Research}
\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py \
  "What is the evidence for intermittent fasting in managing type 2 diabetes in adults? Focus on randomized controlled trials and report HbA1c changes and weight loss outcomes." \
  --model sonar-pro
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Trend Analysis}
\pre{\startverb
python scripts/perplexity_search.py \
  "What are the key trends in single-cell RNA sequencing technology over the past 5 years? Highlight improvements in throughput, cost, and resolution, with specific examples." \
  --model sonar-pro
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Working with Results}
\subtree{
\title{Programmatic Access}
\p{Use \code{\startverb perplexity_search.py\stopverb} as a module:}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.perplexity_search import search_with_perplexity

result = search_with_perplexity(
    query="What are the latest CRISPR developments?",
    model="openrouter/perplexity/sonar-pro",
    max_tokens=4000,
    temperature=0.2,
    verbose=False
)

if result["success"]:
    print(result["answer"])
    print(f"Tokens used: {result['usage']['total_tokens']}")
else:
    print(f"Error: {result['error']}")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Save and Process Results}
\pre{\startverb
# Save to JSON
python scripts/perplexity_search.py "query" --output results.json

# Process with jq
cat results.json | jq '.answer'
cat results.json | jq '.usage'
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Batch Processing}
\p{Create a script for multiple queries:}

\pre{\startverb
#!/bin/bash
queries=(
  "CRISPR developments 2024"
  "mRNA vaccine technology advances"
  "AlphaFold3 accuracy improvements"
)

for query in "${queries[@]}"; do
  echo "Searching: $query"
  python scripts/perplexity_search.py "$query" --output "results_$(echo $query | tr ' ' '_').json"
  sleep 2  # Rate limiting
done
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Cost Management}
\p{Perplexity models have different pricing tiers:}

\p{\strong{Approximate costs per query:}}

\ul{
\li{\startverb Sonar: $0.001-0.002 (most cost-effective)\stopverb}
\li{\startverb Sonar Pro: $0.002-0.005 (recommended default)\stopverb}
\li{\startverb Sonar Reasoning Pro: $0.005-0.010\stopverb}
\li{\startverb Sonar Pro Search: $0.020-0.050+ (most comprehensive)\stopverb}
}

\p{\strong{Cost optimization strategies:}}

\ol{
\li{Use \code{\startverb sonar\stopverb} for simple fact lookups}
\li{Default to \code{\startverb sonar-pro\stopverb} for most queries}
\li{Reserve \code{\startverb sonar-pro-search\stopverb} for complex analysis}
\li{Set \code{\startverb --max-tokens\stopverb} to limit response length}
\li{Monitor usage at https://openrouter.ai/activity}
\li{Set spending limits in OpenRouter dashboard}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting}
\subtree{
\title{API Key Not Set}
\p{\strong{Error}: "OpenRouter API key not configured"}

\p{\strong{Solution}:}

\pre{\startverb
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY='sk-or-v1-your-key-here'
# Or run setup script
python scripts/setup_env.py --api-key sk-or-v1-your-key-here
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{LiteLLM Not Installed}
\p{\strong{Error}: "LiteLLM not installed"}

\p{\strong{Solution}:}

\pre{\startverb
uv pip install litellm
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rate Limiting}
\p{\strong{Error}: "Rate limit exceeded"}

\p{\strong{Solutions}:}

\ul{
\li{Wait a few seconds before retrying}
\li{Increase rate limit at https://openrouter.ai/keys}
\li{Add delays between requests in batch processing}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Insufficient Credits}
\p{\strong{Error}: "Insufficient credits"}

\p{\strong{Solution}:}

\ul{
\li{Add credits at https://openrouter.ai/account}
\li{Enable auto-recharge to prevent interruptions}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/openrouter_setup.md\stopverb} for comprehensive troubleshooting guide.}
}
}

